                     <interp inst="def1-2777-18411025" type="occupation" value="BLACKSMITH"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ROBERT KING</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18411025-2777-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18411025-2777-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18411025-2777-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18411025-cd-197" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18411025-2777-offence-1 t18411025-cd-197"></join>26th of Sep<lb></lb>tember</rs>, 42lbs. weight of copper, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. the goods of <persName id="t18411025-name-1264" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1264" type="surname" value="CRISP"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1264" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18411025-2777-offence-1 t18411025-name-1264"></join>Thomas Crisp</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-1265" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1265" type="surname" value="JOYNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1265" type="given" value="WILLIAM THOMAS"></interp>WILLIAM THOMAS JOYNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Thomas Crisp, of Ber<lb></lb>mondsey—the prisoner was in his employ as a blacksmith. I missed 42lbs. of copper on the 26th of September—it was sent to repair the <hi rend="italic">Flora</hi>—I cannot swear to the copper produced—I had some of this description, and to the best of my belief it is my master's—I missed it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you reason to know there was a person who you could not reach by law, who has been seducing this boy away? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I have, and am instructed by my master to recom<lb></lb>mend the prisoner to mercy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-1266" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1266" type="surname" value="HENDLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1266" type="given" value="JOHN BUDD"></interp>JOHN BUDD HENDLE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 254.) On the 25th of Sep<lb></lb>tember, I met the prisoner with the copper on his shoulder—I asked what he had got in the bag—he said copper, which he was going to take to Capt. Turner, and he brought it from the schooner <hi rend="italic">Flora</hi>—I went with him to Mill-pond—I saw where he said he was going, and could find no such person as Capt. Turner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> He was taken to the Magistrate? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he made a discovery to me about a Jew named Isaacs, and gave me an account of where I could find some property of his master's—Isaacs was taken and allowed to go.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
